  "text": "The heartbeat session timeout flows through two sides: **client-side** and **broker-side (group coordinator)**.\n\n**Threshold definition:**\n- `CommonClientConfigs.java:207` defines `SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG` (\"session.timeout.ms\") \u2014 the client-side config for classic protocol consumers.\n- `ConsumerConfig.java:102` re-exports it for consumer configuration.\n- `GroupCoordinatorConfig.java:155` defines `CONSUMER_GROUP_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG` (\"group.consumer.session.timeout.ms\") with a default of 45000ms \u2014 the broker-side config for the new consumer protocol.\n- `Heartbeat.java:52` creates the `sessionTimer` initialized with `config.sessionTimeoutMs`, and method `sessionTimeoutExpired()` (line 119) checks whether the timer has expired.\n\n**Timeout raised/logged during polling:**\n- `AbstractCoordinator.java:1513-1517` \u2014 In the heartbeat thread's polling loop, when `heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)` is true, it calls `markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\")` \u2014 this is the exact 'Heartbeat session timed out' path on the client side.\n- `GroupMetadataManager.java:6664` \u2014 `expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` is invoked server-side when the heartbeat timer fires, logging member removal on heartbeat expiration (lines 6678-6697).\n- `GroupMetadataManager.java:4452-4463` \u2014 `scheduleConsumerGroupSessionTimeout()` schedules the timer that fences members with \"the member session expired\" when the session timeout elapses without a heartbeat.",
